 My stomach is killing me again.

168
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,000
 I'm going to the doctor.

169
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,000
 Reiko.

170
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,000
 I'll leave the rest to you.

171
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,000
 You're a pretty attractive guy.

172
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 I'm Ryotsu.

173
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
 Nice to meet you.

174
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 Oh.

175
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
 You're the super famous Ryotsu?

176
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,000
 I am.

177
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 I'm Ryotsu.

178
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,000
 Nice to meet you, too.

179
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,000
 You two are the bad guys.

180
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,000
 You two seem to be happy.

181
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:35,000
 Is that helicopter for the next time?

182
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:39,000
 You're rich for the konnyaku shop.

183
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
 Konnyaku shop?

184
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 By the way, why did you become a police officer?

185
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
 Well,

186
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
 I've lived in New York for a long time.

187
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:56,000
 I've always wanted to be a police officer who would risk his life for the citizens.

188
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
 And you're wearing a shabby uniform.

189
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,000
 What?

190
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 That's right.

191
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 I think it's more problematic than a gun.

192
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 Is that so?

193
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 The uniform of the police in Japan is not good.

194
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
 So I made an order in Armani.

195
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,000
 It was about 1 million yen.

196
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,000
 1 million yen?

197
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,000
 I don't think I can afford such a cheap uniform.

198
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:31,000
 I don't know how you feel about spending 300,000 yen on a radio.

199
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
 I'll do it with you.

200
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,000
 Yes, yes.

201
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 By the way,

202
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,000
 I haven't been going to the police recently, but I've been trying to forgive you for that kind of uniform.

203
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:44,000
 Well, I was told it was no good, but I changed my clothes on the helicopter.

204
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,000
 I'll do that.

205
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
 The chief should be in pain, too.

206
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,000
 I'll go to the patrol.

207
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:56,000
 Ryo-chan, tell Mr. Nakagawa.

208
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,000
 See you later.

209
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,000
 So what should I do?

210
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
 I'll tell you.

211
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 You're the one who teaches me.

212
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,000
 I'll go to the patrol, too.

213
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,000
 Hey.

214
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,000
 Damn it.

215
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,000
 Well, I...

216
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:17,000
 Stand in front of me and show me the way.

217
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
 Yes, sir.

218
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:27,000
 Are you Mr. Omawari?

219
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,000
 Yes, I am.

220
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,000
 Oh, good.

221
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:33,000
 I'd like to ask you the way.

222
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,000
 Yes, please.

223
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,000
 Senpai, please wake up.

224
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,000
 What is it?

225
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,000
 I was sleeping well.

226
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:50,000
 I was asked the way, but I don't know anything about this area.

227
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
 What?

228
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,000
 What?

229
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,000
 Show me the map and let me look for it.

230
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 That's the old man who came back to Japan for the first time in 50 years.

231
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:02,000
 He says he doesn't know where this is.

232
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,000
 Well, it can't be helped.

233
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,000
 So, where do you want to go?

234
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,000
 A restaurant.

235
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 What kind of restaurant?

236
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:15,000
 I forgot the name of the restaurant, but I have a clue.

237
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,000
 What?

238
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,000
 It's a restaurant like this.

239
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,000
 Oh, that's a bad picture.

240
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,000
 Did you draw it?

241
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:28,000
 When I was a student, it was more than 50 years ago.

242
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,000
 What? 50 years ago?

243
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,000
 So, what's the address of the restaurant?

244
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:37,000
 That's the downtown of Tokyo.

245
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,000
 That's all?

246
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,000
 Yes.

247
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,000
 No, no.

248
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,000
 The downtown is big.

249
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,000
 I don't understand.

250
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,000
 Give up.

251
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 That's no good.

252
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,000
 Because it's my first job.

253
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 Do whatever you want.

254
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:55,000
 If you let me look for it, I would like to thank you.

255
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,000
 What?

256
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
 Why don't you say that first?

257
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,000
 I'll ask you about the details in the back.

258
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,000
 Hey, Nakagawa.

259
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 Order coffee and cake for breakfast.

260
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,000
 What?

261
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,000
 Just go.

262
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,000
 Yes.

263
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 I see.

264
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 When I was a high school student, I went to that restaurant several times.

265
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,000
 High school?

266
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,000
 Yes.

267
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,000
 It's Tokyo Art University now.

268
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,000
 I was always busy because I had a day off.

269
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,000
 What?

270
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
 That means it's near the art college.

271
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,000
 Yes.

272
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:32,000
 I walked for about 15 minutes.

273
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:35,000
 The art college is on the upper floor.

274
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 If you don't mind, I'll have this.

275
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,000
 Sorry.

276
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:45,000
 Let's look for it near the art college.

277
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:49,000
 Can you find it in about two hours?

278
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,000
 If it's on the upper floor, it'll take 20 to 30 minutes by car.

279
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:58,000
 Actually, I have to go back to Paris by the 1 o'clock flight to Narita.

280
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:04,000
 If it's on the upper floor, it'll take about an hour in Tokyo.

281
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,000
 What?

282
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,000
 Get a taxi.

283
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 I'll call you right away.

284
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,000
 It's me.

285
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:14,000
 Bring the car to the airport right away.

286
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,000
 Well...

287
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,000
 How about my car?

288
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,000
 Thank you very much.

289
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,000
 Here it is.

290
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 Ferrari F40.

291
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 Here you are.

292
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,000
 But this is for two people.

293
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,000
 I've remodeled it into a new one, so it's okay.

294
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 Please get in.

295
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
 Reiko, I'm back at a good place.

296
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,000
 Ryo-chan.

297
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,000
 I need help.

298
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,000
 I need a taxi.

299
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,000
 What?

300
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,000
 See you later.

301
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:56,000
 I think I saw him somewhere.

302
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,000
 I'm back at the airport.

303
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
 Damn it.

304
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
 I don't have time for this.

305
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 Hey, Nakagawa.

306
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,000
 Turn around.

307
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,000
 Senpai, it's impossible.

308
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,000
 Is it the exit of the one-way street?

309
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,000
 Idiot!

310
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 Don't you want to make a good old man's wish come true?

311
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,000
 Well...

312
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,000
 Go back.

313
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 Then there's no problem.

314
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,000
 No way.

315
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,000
 I understand.

316
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 Senpai, let's go back.

317
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
 What's going on?

318
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
 Idiot!

319
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,000
 I don't know.

320
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 Ryoji Kankichi.

321
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,000
 He's back at it again.

322
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:54,000
 It's nice to ride such a lovely car.

323
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,000
 It's not the time to be impressed.

324
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,000
 I'll arrest you this time.

325
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 Turn left.

326
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,000
 Stop.

327
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,000
 Senpai, what should we do?

328
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,000
 When you're busy...

329
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,000
 Come on!

330
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
 I'll show you the power of Ferrari.

331
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,000
 Yes, sir.

332
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 It's too fast.

333
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 It's Ryoji Kankichi again.

334
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 If there's a problem, I'll fix it.

335
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,000
 Turn right.

336
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 Yes, sir.

337
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,000
 Turn left.

338
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 Yes, sir.

339
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
 But Ryoji is so busy.

340
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,000
 I can see it well.

341
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:40,000
 I've been playing around here since I was a kid.

342
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,000
 It's like a garden.

343
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
 It's impossible to go any further.

344
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 Idiot!

345
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
 It's your first job.

346
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:56,000
 Policemen always finish their tasks.

347
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,000
 Senpai.

348
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 I made a mistake.

349
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,000
 All right.

350
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
 It's getting darker.

351
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,000
 Don't worry.

352
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 I can get through.

353
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 I've been here before.

354
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 It's not a bicycle.

355
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,000
 All right.

356
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,000
 As expected of Senpai.

357
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,000
 What is this place?

358
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 Can you stop for a moment?

359
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,000
 It's nostalgic.

360
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,000
 I've lived in Paris for decades.

361
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,000
 I often remember Japan.

362
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:45,000
 It was when I was a student at a beautiful art school.

363
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 I was surrounded by good friends.

364
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,000
 I was painting all day long.

365
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 Ueno is a forest of art.

366
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,000
 I went to the art museum every day.

367
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,000
 I had a good time with my friends.

368
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 At that time, I fell in love with the girl at the cafeteria that my friend took me to.

369
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 It was my first love.

370
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,000
 That's the cafeteria in that painting.

371
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 When was that?

372
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 I think it was close to graduation.

373
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:22,000
 It was when I caught a cold and went to bed.

374
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,000
 She came to the dormitory.

375
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:28,000
 She took care of me.

376
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 When I got better, I tried to thank her.

377
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:42,000
 At that time, I was poor and had no money to give her a present.

378
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:47,000
 So I drew her portrait with all my heart.

379
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:50,000
 And I gave her that picture.

380
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:59,000
 The happy face of that girl at that time is still burning in my eyes.

381
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 So what is that girl?

382
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 I went to study in Paris at the same time as graduation.

383
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,000
 I didn't say I liked her.

384
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:12,000
 It's a long time ago.

385
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,000
 It's not the time to be upset.

386
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,000
 There's only an hour left.

387
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,000
 Let's find the cafeteria.

388
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 How is it, old man?

389
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 Do you remember the scenery around here?

390
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 This area has changed a lot since 50 years ago.

391
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 An hour left?

392
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 It's impossible.

393
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:56,000
 I decided to bring back my memories to Paris as a memory.

394
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 There are still 10 minutes left.

395
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 I won't give up.

396
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 I won't give up.

397
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,000
 I can't find one or two of them.

398
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 I'm going to be a police officer.

399
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 Damn it!

400
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:17,000
 I've been thinking about you for 50 years.

401
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 I wanted to see you for the first time.

402
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 It's okay.

403
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,000
 This is also fate.

404
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 That tree...

405
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,000
 I found it!

406
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
 I found it!

407
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 Look at this place.

408
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,000
 It's the same as before.

409
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 It hasn't changed at all.

410
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 Let's go see the first love.

411
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 Wait a minute.

412
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,000
 What's wrong, old man?

413
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 He's married and has a family.

414
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
 I don't want to ask him all of a sudden.

415
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
 What are you talking about?

416
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,000
 Let's go inside.

417
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,000
 But...

418
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:01,000
 If you don't open it, I'll open it.

419
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 Come on.

420
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,000
 Open it.

421
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,000
 Hurry up and open it.

422
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
 Ms. Isumi.

423
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 Mr. Taki.

424
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,000
 It's Mr. Taki, right?

425
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,000
 Yes.

426
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
 It's been a long time.

427
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 No, it's true.

428
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 That painting is still in the store.

429
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:40,000
 You've been taking good care of it.

430
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:44,000
 This painting is my treasure.

431
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 Thank you, Ms. Isumi.

432
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 Senpai, look at that happy face.

433
00:21:56,000 --> 00:22:00,000
 We police officers work hard for the people's smiles.

434
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 Police officers have a great job.

435
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 By the way, how much will you give me?

436
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,000
 Senpai.

437
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 No, thanks to you, I made a good memory.

438
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:17,000
 Please accept this as a thank you.

439
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
 Thank you.

440
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 Then I'll take care of it.

441
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Goodbye.

442
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,000
 Let's go home.

443
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,000
 Are you going again?

444
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 There's nothing to be happy about.

445
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:41,000
 I got such a bad painting.

446
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,000
 Hey, idiot.

447
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 I'll do this painting.

448
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,000
 Is it okay?

449
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,000
 It's okay.

450
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 Go.

451
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 Taki, Jotaro.

452
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 Did the Ferrari just break down?

453
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 No, it didn't.

454
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,000
 We still have a lot of cars.

455
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:08,000
 Do you have that much money?

456
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 Well, it's about 400 million yen.

457
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,000
 400 million yen?

458
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:17,000
 Nakagawa, let's get along.

459
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,000
 Ryo-chan.

460
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 There was an old man in the Ferrari, right?

461
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 Yes, that old man.

462
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,000
 No way.

463
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 He was a famous painter all over the world.

464
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,000
 It's that old man, right?

465
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:34,000
 Is he such a famous painter?

466
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:38,000
 One painting costs at least 100 million yen.

467
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 100 million yen?

468
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
 I won.

469
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
 You're good.

470
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:48,000
 I'll give you a lot of money.

471
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,000
 My 100 million yen.

472
00:23:55,000 --> 00:24:02,000
 Subbed by Dreadopp and Zedopp.

473
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 I've come up with an amazing idea.

474
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 I'm going to sell ramen on a balloon.

475
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,000
 I mean, a convenience store.

476
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 What do you think?

477
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 No one can come up with such a great idea.

478
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:18,000
 I'm a genius.

479
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:21,000
 Next time, on Sky Jumping Store.

480
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 I'm looking forward to it.

481
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:55,000
 Hey, smile at me

482
00:24:55,000 --> 00:25:00,000
 You're not bad

483
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 Hey, smile at me

484
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 You're doing great

485
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:12,000
 Smile at me all the time

486
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:17,000
 A serious woman is not beautiful

487
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:23,000
 You should smile right away

488
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:27,000
 If you're not a child
